@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="py-4">
    <h1 class="mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">CineTrack is a student project built for educational purposes at the University of Cincinnati.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Data We Collect</h4>
    <p>CineTrack stores only the movie information you submit through the Add a Movie form, including title, genre, release year, rating, and description. No personal information is collected, stored, or shared.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">How Data Is Used</h4>
    <p>Submitted movie data is stored in a local SQL Server database and used solely to populate the Top 100 list and genre browsing pages within this application.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Third-Party Services</h4>
    <p>This site uses Bootstrap and jQuery loaded from the local library. No external tracking, analytics, or advertising services are used.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Contact</h4>
    <p>This project was developed by Aiden Hartranft, Danielle Hart, and Nick Turner as part of a Web Application Development course at the University of Cincinnati.</p>
</div>
